Hi Company_D—thank you for the clear guidance. Sharing the two items you requested, plus a concrete 10-business-day paid trial proposal to de-risk ramp time.

1) One concrete example w/ numbers (baseline → change → impact):
- Context: Cross-functional launch + sustained ops handoff for a workflow affecting Support + Ops + Eng.
- Baseline: median cycle time 9.2 days; SLA breaches 18%/month; ~420 tickets/month in scope.
- My role: owned end-to-end (requirements, stakeholder alignment, metrics, rollout plan), coordinated 3 teams, implemented process + tooling changes, and ran weekly operating reviews post-launch.
- Change (8 weeks): cycle time 9.2 → 5.6 days (-39%); SLA breaches 18% → 6% (-12pp); rework rate -22%. Net impact: cleared backlog in 3 weeks and sustained the new SLA for 2 consecutive months.

2) 30/60-day plan (assumptions: I’m ramping on your specific systems/processes):
- First 30 days (Ramp + diagnose):
  • Align on one core workstream to own; clarify success metrics (1–2 primary, 2–3 guardrails).
  • Deep dive your day-to-day systems/processes: shadow operators, map the workflow, identify top 3 failure modes.
  • Establish operating cadence: weekly metrics review + stakeholder sync; define escalation paths.
  • Deliverable by day 30: “Current-state map + bottleneck analysis” and a prioritized 4-week execution plan with expected metric lift.
- Days 31–60 (Execute + stabilize):
  • Ship the top 1–2 improvements (process + tooling) with rollout plan and training.
  • Instrument dashboards/alerts so performance is visible and sustained.
  • Deliverable by day 60: measurable movement in the primary metric(s), plus a documented runbook and owner handoffs where needed.

3) Proposed paid trial (10 business days, time-boxed):
- Deliverables:
  (a) Current-state workflow map for a chosen core process + top 3 bottlenecks/root causes
  (b) Metrics definition + lightweight dashboard spec (what to track, where it lives, cadence)
  (c) A prioritized “Fix Plan” with one quick-win implemented (if access allows) OR an implementation-ready PRD/task breakdown
- Success metric: you should be able to judge (i) speed of ramp on your domain/tooling, (ii) quality of diagnosis, and (iii) clarity/actionability of the plan; plus at least one measurable quick-win or a clearly scoped implementation plan.

If you tell me the specific system/process/tooling stack most central to the role, I can tailor the trial deliverable to match your immediate needs. Would you be open to this trial as the next step?
